# Cursor Development Rules

## Data Sources

- DO NOT use mock data in any implementation
- Always implement real API calls to retrieve data from the blockchain
- Use Monad testnet for all blockchain interactions
- Connect to actual Nad.fun contracts and APIs for token information
- Use viem client to make direct RPC calls to the Monad network

## Implementation Guidelines

- Focus on real-time data retrieval and processing
- Implement proper error handling for API failures
- Use caching strategically for performance, not for avoiding real data
- Ensure all tools return actual blockchain data
- Prioritize accuracy of token information over convenience

## Development Priorities

- Real blockchain integration is highest priority
- API design should match real-world usage patterns
- Testing should use actual Monad testnet, not mock responses
